{"id":"joiakim","term":"Joiakim","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>(whom Jehovah has set up) = Jehoiakim, a high priest, the son and successor of Jeshua (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Nehemiah 12:10\">Neh. 12:10</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Nehemiah 12:12\">12</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Nehemiah 12:26\">26</a>).</p>\n\u0000","refs":["Nehemiah 12:10","Nehemiah 12:12","Nehemiah 12:26"]}